t-family: Merriweather, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 400; white-space: normal;\\\"><h1 class=\\\"entry-title\\\" style=\\\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 400; line-height: 38px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-transform: capitalize; overflow: hidden; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 30px !important;\\\">Diet And Cure For Candida Infections<\\/h1><\\/header>\",\"align\":\"left\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"439269f\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"<h2 data-elementor-setting-key=\\\"title\\\" data-pen-placeholder=\\\"Type Here...\\\" style=\\\"letter-spacing: normal;\\\"><div style=\\\"overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Merriweather, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 400; white-space: normal;\\\"><section style=\\\"float: left; width: 870px; clear: both;\\\"><div style=\\\"width: 870px; max-width: 1170px; margin: 0px auto; padding-left: 15px; padding-right: 15px;\\\"><div style=\\\"display: flex; width: calc(100% + 30px); flex-wrap: wrap; margin-left: -15px; margin-right: -15px; clear: both;\\\"><div style=\\\" min-height: 1px; position: relative; padding: 0px; clear: none;\\\"><div style=\\\"clear: both; height: 449.5px;\\\"><div style=\\\"display: inline-block; clear: both; padding: 0px 0px;\\\"><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\"><em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;is a term that refers to a large family of yeasts (one celled fungi) that under normal circumstances, harmlessly inhabit the tissues of humans. &nbsp; This is because a balanced intestinal tract from mouth to colon contains a preponderance of beneficial bacteria that keep&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;in check.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\">When not enough beneficial bacteria are present in a given body tissue to keep&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;under control,&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;transforms from a harmless state into an invasive species. &nbsp;In this rapidly growing state,&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;puts out long stringy hyphae or \\u201croots\\u201d which can penetrate through the tissues of the body.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\"><em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;overgrowth can occur in many tissues of the body such as oral candidiasis known as thrush, &nbsp;the scalp as dandruff, or vaginal yeast infections.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: 700;\\\">What Causes&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;Overgrowth?<\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\"><em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;is an opportunistic pathogen that can rapidly take over when a person is under a course of antibiotics. &nbsp;Antibiotics decimate beneficial gut flora but have little effect on&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>, giving this normally harmless yeast the chance to take over dominance of the gut environment very quickly.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\">Many women don\\u2019t realize it, but oral contraceptives imbalance the gut in the same way as antibiotics giving&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;an open door to take control.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-bottom: 10.5px; line-height: 23px;\\\">A diet of processed foods high in sugars and simple carbohydrates also encourages&nbsp;<em>Candida<\\/em>&nbsp;overgrowth as yeasts thrive on sugars.<span style=\\\"color: rgb(110, 193, 228); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 1.75em; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0px; white-space: pre-wrap;\\\"><\\/span><\\/p><\\/div><\\/div><\\/div><\\/div><\\/div><\\/section><\\/div><\\/h2>\",\"align\":\"left\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"1f2e69c\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"content_width\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":1140},\"gap\":\"wider\",\"structure\":\"30\",\"background_overlay_title\":\"\",\"paddi